x4freetext: Split-pole spectrometer using an array of
Cross sections obtained by assuming that the strongest
transition seen is the analog of the ground state of
the target nucleus.  Other levels which could
correspond to analogs of low-lying states of the
Excitation energy is deduced from the (3He,t) Q-values
and the (p,n) Q-values to the ground state, which are
taken either from the tables of Mattauch or from the
values of Freemean, see related references.
